  "summary": "Heavily obfuscated bundles in ai-node-agent require human review",
  "details": "The package ships multiple heavily obfuscated JavaScript bundles under dist/ (client.js, server.js, react.js, index.js, and two hashed chunks) using the _0x\u003chex\u003e identifier scheme characteristic of javascript-obfuscator output. A pattern match on dist/server.js also flagged keyword co-occurrence of 'ping' and 'GET' alongside identifier-like tokens, but the surrounding code could not be traced through the obfuscation to confirm intent or destination. The package presents itself as an AI agent runtime; obfuscation of all shipped bundles is a transparency concern that prevents verification of whether the bundles perform only the advertised function or also collect/transmit caller data. No concrete attacker infrastructure, credential-path reads, lifecycle-script droppers, or install-time network calls were observed. Recommend human review to deobfuscate and verify the network behavior of dist/server.js and the contents of dist/client.js before trusting the package.",
